revision.text:
On the night of 28 October 2014, at 22.00 the [[Republic of Macedonia]] government building was attacked with what is believed to have been two [[rocket propelled grenade]]s (RPG), damaging the walls and roof of the building. No casualties were reported. It has been speculated that the event is linked to the recent proclamation of the so-called "[[Republic of Ilirida]]".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.b92.net/eng/news/region.php?yyyy=2014&mm=10&dd=31&nav_id=92097 |title=B92 - News - Reports: RPGs used in attack on government HQ |work=B92 |accessdate=5 December 2014 |date=31 October 2014 |language=English}}</ref> The same building was attacked by RPGs in 2007. The [[National Liberation Army (Albanians of Macedonia)|National Liberation Army]] (NLA), the militant organization that fought against the Macedonian government in the [[Insurgency in the Republic of Macedonia]] (2001), claimed responsibly for the attack.<ref name=Balkan-insight>{{cite web |author=Sinisa Jakov Marusic |url=http://www.balkaninsight.com/en/article/new-%C3%ACliberation-army%C3%AE-claims-attack-on-macedonian-government-hq |title='Liberation Army' Claims it Shelled Macedonian Govt|publisher=balkaninsight.com |accessdate=5 December 2014 |date=7 November 2014 |language=English}}</ref> In a press release published by Alsat M, an Albanian-language TV station in Macedonia, and signed by "Commander Kushtrim", the organization claimed that the "Hasan Prishtina" elite force hit the government building in a coordinated action.<ref name=Balkan-insight/> The organization claims it is "discontented" with the 2001 [[Ohrid Agreement]] peace plan.<ref name=Balkan-insight/> {{Campaignbox Insurgency in Macedonia}}
==Aftermath== On 21 April 2015, a group of 40 armed men with NLA patches [[Goshince attack|attacked the border police station at Goshince]]. The group tied the policemen and beat them, then stole the arms and communication devices; they stayed for a couple of hours, filming the event, and before they left for Kosovo, they issued this message through an interpreter: {{cquote|We are from the [[National Liberation Army (Albanians of Macedonia)|National Liberation Army]]. Tell them that neither [[Ali Ahmeti]] nor [[Nikola Gruevski]] can save you. We do not want any [[Ohrid Agreement|framework agreement]] and if we see you here again, we will kill you. We want our own state."<ref name=B92>{{cite news |url=http://www.b92.net/info/vesti/index.php?yyyy=2015&mm=04&dd=21&nav_category=167&nav_id=983125 |title=MKD: Teroristi OVK upali u karaulu|date=21 April 2015 |publisher=B92|id= |language=sr |accessdate=3 May 2015}}</ref><ref name=Focus>{{cite news |url=http://www.focus-fen.net/news/2015/04/21/370083/plus-info-macedonia-terrorists-with-national-liberation-army-attack-police-station-in-gosince.html |title=Plus info, Macedonia: Terrorists with National Liberation Army attack police station in Gosince |date=21 April 2015 |publisher=FOCUS News Agency |id= |accessdate=3 May 2015}}</ref><ref name=RTS>{{cite news|url=http://www.rts.rs/page/stories/ci/story/3/%D0%A0%D0%B5%D0%B3%D0%B8%D0%BE%D0%BD/1895591/|title=Македонска полиција повратила караулу коју је јутрос заузео УЧК |last=Maroevic |first=Rade |date=21 April 2015|publisher=RTS |language=sr |accessdate=3 May 2015}}</ref>}}
A [[Kumanovo clashes|shootout erupted]] during a [[police raid]] between [[Law enforcement in the Republic of Macedonia|police forces]] and an armed group identifying as the NLA occurred on 9 May 2015 in the northern town of [[Kumanovo]].
