{{About|a ruler||Mir Ali (disambiguation){{!}}Mir Ali}}
{{unsourced|date=February 2009}}
'''Mir Ali Murad Talpur''', known as the ''Aadil-i-Jang'', was the second ruler of the Mankani [[Talpur]]s state of Mirpurkhas. He founded [[Mirpurkhas]] town in 1806 and made it the capital of his state which was founded by his father, [[Mir Tharo Khan Talpur]] at Keti Mir Tharo. His state included territories of the present day southeastern [[Sindh]]. His son, [[Mir Sher Muhammad Talpur]] pioneered the freedom struggle of Sindh after the fall of [[Hyderabad, Pakistan|Hyderabad]] in February 1843 at the hands of British invaders.

