{{Infobox language family |name=Baga |ethnicity= |region=coastal [[Guinea]] |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Mel languages|Mel]] |fam4=Temne |child1=Landoma |child2=Baga proper |glotto=none |glotto2=temn1245 |glottoname2=Temne–Baga }}
The '''Baga languages''' are languages of the [[Mel languages|Mel]] family spoken in the coastal region of [[Guinea]]. The total number of speakers is about 30,000, of which Landoma speakers make up almost half.
==Languages== The varieties apart from Landoma are sometimes considered dialects of one language, ''Baga'' or ''Barka''. Landoma is somewhat more distantly related.
*[[Landoma language|Landoma]] *[[Baga language|Baga]]: Binari, Koba, Manduri, Sitemú, etc.
The Baga languages are in turn related to [[Temne language|Temne]], one of the four official languages of [[Sierra Leone]]; together, Baga and Temne belong to the [[Mel languages|Mel branch]] of [[Niger–Congo languages]].
